-- Colombia’s Isagen Plans New Projects, CEO Rico Tells Republica
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-02-03T13:30:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/colombia-s-isagen-plans-new-projects-ceo-rico-tells-republica.html
Isagen SA (ISAGEN) , a Colombian state-
controlled power producer, is planning new energy projects with
a total capacity of 3,500 megawatts, Chief Executive Officer
Luis Fernando Rico told  La Republica  newspaper.  The Medellin-based company, will get $79 million a year
when  Colombia ’s 800 megawatt Hidrosogamoso hydroelectric plant
begins to operate in 2013, Rico told the daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  